  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "b is a disposition means: b is a realizable entity & b’s bearer is some material entity & b is such that if it ceases to exist, then its bearer is physically changed, & b’s realization occurs when and because this bearer is in some special physical circumstances, & this realization occurs in virtue of the bearer’s physical make-up. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [062-002])"
  } ]
